<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="19" pageId="7" pageNumber="18" type="type-locality">
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="18">Type-locality.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="19" pageId="7" pageNumber="18">
Peru: Madre De Dios, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Río">Rio</normalizedToken>
La Torre, Tambopata Res., 
<geoCoordinate direction="south" orientation="latitude" precision="15" value="-12.836945">12°50'13&quot;S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate direction="west" orientation="longitude" precision="15" value="-69.29305">69°17'35&quot;W</geoCoordinate>
, 300 m. Tambopata is at the mouth of the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Río">Rio</normalizedToken>
La Torre. In 1986 there was a lodge and a network of trails through uncut wet lowland forest. The holotype 
<pageBreakToken pageId="8" pageNumber="19" start="start">was</pageBreakToken>
collected during the transition between the dry and wet seasons when butterfly abundance and diversity generally peak.
</paragraph>
